 
<p>
 The European Parliament approved a plan to direct some of the funds
 meant for decarbonization into 
<a href="https://www.commondreams.org/news/2022/07/06/betrayal-uproar-after-eu-backs-industry-push-label-gas-and-nuclear-green">natural gas development instead.</a>
<p>
 Counting the inevitable methane leaks, 
<a href="https://www.alternet.org/2016/01/methane-madness-porter-ranch-only-tip-iceberg-exposing-catastrophic-impacts-natural-gas/">natural gas is as bad as coal.</a>
<p>
 The same plan allows for spending on nuclear power plants, too.  While
 they do not emit greenhouse gas, they create the danger of nuclear
 accidents. Because of their great expense, 
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/nov/27/uks-nuclear-sites-costing-taxpayers-astronomical-sums-say-mps">this is a terribly
inefficient way to decarbonize.</a>

 